==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''deletus'', p.p. of ''delere'' "destroy, blot out, efface," from ''delevi'', originally perf. tense of ''delinere'' "to daub, erase by smudging," from ''de-'' "from, away" + ''linere'' "to smear, wipe."

===Transitive verb===
'''to delete''', '''[[deleting]]''', '''[[deleted]]'''
# [[remove]], get rid of, [[erase]]

